	(text "TODO: \n\n- Implement FT232H with SPI capibility (CLK, SER_IN, SER_OUT)\n	FT232H has its own chip select (CS) line as well. Probably driven internally by onboard SPI controller. (Not sure, verify)\n	This could be used for pin G1A of the decoder to save a GPIO\n	Need to determine which parts of the example schematic need to be kept\n	\n\n- Implement and label the following GPIO's on the FT232H:\n	GPIO 0-3 (CS decoder input)\n	AMP_ON (Enable pin of V_PD/+1.8V LDO)\n	\n	Maybe: If +/- 5V LDOs or another power component has an enable pin, maybe a PWR_ON GPIO to power down the whole board?\n\n\n- Implement new power system:\n	Barrel jack input (+9 or +12V)\n	To high efficiency switching regulator (down to +6 or so volts)\n\n	For +5V:\n		+6V into LDO. \n		Maybe: RC filter before LDO input for some switching noise attenuation. \n			(If we do this, components MUST be high current)\n\n	For -5V:\n		+6V into charge pump inverter (need to be careful with this. They can be noisy)\n		Output of that into negative LDO.\n		\n		\n	"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 281.432 278.638 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "ba50e2d2-591d-49bf-925e-211d3427eb22")
	)
